or runtime state directories.\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-130-\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-131-### `cloche health`\n--\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-564-\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-565-```\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-566-my-project/\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-567-├── .cloche/\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-568-│   ├── develop.cloche        # Container workflow definition\ndocs/USAGE.md:569:│   ├── host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow (runs on host)\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-570-│   ├── Dockerfile            # Container image\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-571-│   ├── config.toml           # Project configuration (orchestration, evolution)\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-572-│   ├── prompts/\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-573-│   │   ├── implement.md      # Prompt templates\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md-574-│   │   ├── fix.md\n--\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-4-\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-5-## Workflow Locations\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-6-\ndocs/workflows.md-7-Cloche distinguishes two workflow locations based on the file they live in:\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-8-\ndocs/workflows.md:9:**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) — Run inside a Docker\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-10-container via `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type. These are the\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-11-standard workflows for coding tasks.\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-12-\ndocs/workflows.md:13:**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) — Runs on the host machine as the daemon\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-14-process. Steps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow` step type\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-15-dispatches a container workflow run and waits for it to complete. This is the extension\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-16-point for custom orchestration strategies.\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md-17-\ndocs/workflows.md-18-The convention is enforced at parse time: a `workflow_name` step in a container workflow\n--\n/workspace/docs/workflows.